The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sunday, February 27, 2005 

 Invest lure for Siliguri

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Siliguri, Feb. 26: The Siliguri Jalpaiguri Development Authority and the Siliguri Municipal Corporation, in collaboration with the Confederation of Indian Industry, will jointly organise a meeting in Siliguri to woo investors.

 The investors? meet will be on the lines of Destination North Bengal, held in February 2003 at Siliguri. The meet for investors from across the country is to take place in April, though the date is yet to be finalised.

 Asok Bhattacharya, the CPM legislator from Siliguri, said here today that the meet would have participation from all sections. ?It will be a collective effort and we will invite MPs from all over North Bengal to interact with investors and understand their needs.?

 The government?s focus is on infrastructural development of the region, which is a must for investment to flow in, said Bhattacharya, the urban development minister. ?For investment to flow in, there is a need for a better infrastructure and we are working on how that can be achieved.?




